✒ Changelog:
    - 1.0.1 (2026-06-21) [Anthropic - Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context)] — Add MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE so exports can land in a browsable public folder.
    - 1.0.0 (2026-06-17) [Anthropic - Claude Opus 4.8] — Initial scaffold + full-standard docstring.

✒ Description:
    The manifest is the app's "ID card + contract" that Android reads before
    running any code: it declares the permissions the app needs, the components
    it contains (Application, Activities, FileProvider), and how the system
    launches it. Nothing here is optional boilerplate — Android refuses to grant
    a permission or open a screen that isn't declared.

✒ Key Features:
    - uses-permission: READ_SMS (covers both SMS and MMS providers) plus optional READ_CONTACTS for number-to-name resolution; "dangerous" perms still require runtime grant in MainActivity.
    - MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE: sideload-only All Files access so exports land in a browsable /sdcard/MessageVault/ folder visible to the Files app and OneDrive.
    - application name=".MessageVaultApp": points Android at the Application subclass; the bootstrap android:theme prevents a white flash before Compose takes over.
    - MAIN + LAUNCHER intent-filter on the exported MainActivity: registers the launcher icon and entry point.
    - FileProvider: serves the zipped run to other apps over a content:// URI for Share.

✒ Other Important Information:
    - Dependencies: androidx.core.content.FileProvider; @xml/file_paths; @style/Theme.MessageVault; @mipmap/ic_launcher; @string/app_name.
    - Compatible platforms: Android (minSdk 29, compileSdk 35), JVM 21.
    - Play Store note: READ_SMS is a restricted permission, but this is a sideload-only personal tool, so Play Console policy never applies — permissions are granted on-device.
─────────
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools">

    <!--
      READ_SMS covers reading both the SMS *and* MMS content providers.
      READ_CONTACTS is optional — only used to resolve phone numbers to names.
      No storage permission needed: exports land in app-specific external files
      (getExternalFilesDir), which is world-pullable via file manager / adb.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_SMS" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_CONTACTS" />

    <!--
      Personal SIDELOAD: All files access lets exports land in a browsable
      /sdcard/MessageVault/ folder the Files app and OneDrive can actually see,
      instead of the scoped-storage-hidden Android/data sandbox. Granted on-device
      via Settings (see ExportLocation + MainActivity); never a Play concern here.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"
        tools:ignore="ScopedStorage" />

    <!--
      Progress for long jobs (zipping a run with hundreds of attachments can take a
      while). Runtime-granted on API 33+; denial only costs the status entry.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS" />

    <!--
      A long export must survive the user leaving the app. A foreground service keeps
      the process alive for the run; "dataSync" is the type that matches archiving, and
      API 34+ requires the matching typed permission alongside FOREGROUND_SERVICE.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_DATA_SYNC" />

    <application
        android:name=".MessageVaultApp"
        android:allowBackup="false"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.MessageVault"
        tools:targetApi="35">

        <activity
            android:name=".MainActivity"
            android:exported="true"
            android:label="@string/app_name"
            android:theme="@style/Theme.MessageVault">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- Runs the archive engine so a long export isn't killed when backgrounded. -->
        <service
            android:name=".service.ExportService"
            android:exported="false"
            android:foregroundServiceType="dataSync" />

        <!-- Serves the zipped run to other apps (Share) via a content:// URI. -->
        <provider
            android:name="androidx.core.content.FileProvider"
            android:authorities="${applicationId}.fileprovider"
            android:exported="false"
            android:grantUriPermissions="true">
            <meta-data
                android:name="android.support.FILE_PROVIDER_PATHS"
                android:resource="@xml/file_paths" />
        </provider>
    </application>
</manifest>
